    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Cut your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-a-la-meuniere/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> and <strong>peeled garlic</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-a-la-meuniere/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> into 2 wedges per person</p><p>Squeeze the juice of <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lemon quarters </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) into a small bowl</p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-a-la-meuniere/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [6 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to a large plate with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Press your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> into the<strong> flour</strong>, so they are evenly coated (make sure to shake off any excess!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-a-la-meuniere/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once the potatoes are fork-tender, add the<strong> spinach</strong> to the pot and cook for a further 1 min or until it's wilted</p><p>Drain everything and return to the pot, then mash together with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>garlic</strong> <strong>mash</strong></p><p>Season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then cover to keep warm until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-a-la-meuniere/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated basa</strong> and cook on a high heat for 3-4 min on each side until golden and cooked through</p><p>Once cooked transfer the <strong>basa</strong> to a plate, cover loosely with<strong> tin foil</strong> and set aside</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-a-la-meuniere/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wipe the pan clean with kitchen paper and return it to a medium heat</p><p>Add 30g <span class=\"text-purple\">[45g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g] </span><strong>butter</strong> to the pan and heat until melted, foaming and lightly browned, swirling the pan around, for approx. 1 min</p><p>Remove the pan from the heat and add the<strong> lemon juice</strong>, <strong>capers</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>parsley </strong>and gently stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>lemon caper butter</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-a-la-meuniere/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cooked basa </strong>over the <strong>garlic</strong> <strong>mash</strong> and spoon the <strong>lemon caper butter</strong> all over</p><p>Garnish with a <strong>remaining lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
